# Security

## Secrets
- Never hardcode credentials, API keys, or connection strings
- Load from environment variables, Keychain (Swift), or Databricks secret scopes
- `.env` files for local dev only, never committed to source control

## Input Validation
- Validate all user input at trust boundaries
- SQL: parameterized queries only — no f-string interpolation
- Pydantic `BaseModel` for data crossing trust boundaries (API input, config, external data)

## PHI / PII
- Never log PHI, PII, or credentials at any log level
- Error messages must not leak sensitive data to end users
- Default to principle of least privilege for database connections and API scopes

## Pre-Commit Check
Before any commit, verify:
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets in diff
- [ ] All user inputs validated
- [ ] SQL injection prevention (parameterized queries)
- [ ] Error messages don't leak internals
